  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I must be having a little cold.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Look at me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were in this brick factory for four weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And during that time, we had to sleep in little slats-- were under a, under a, under long strips of-- they're not rooms, they're not houses, they were, they were used to dry out the bricks.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so there were bricks for walls, not necessarily all the way to the, to the top, to the roof.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It just had roof, a roof, and it had beams here and there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It had no natural walls, so it was totally open.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was, this is important to explain because it was April-- April 15, 1944 when we were picked up and for-- during this month that-- for four weeks that we were in ghetto [NON-ENGLISH], the strong wind, a sharp, cold wind, swept through the ghetto, and the red brick dust was all over us.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It didn't take perhaps not even more than an hour before the red dust just, just penetrated every part of your body, even the area that was covered up.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It, it was incredible how the wind would sweep this red dust.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What would-- what was a very nice factory, as factories go, and in fact, a fairly new factory [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was not for the purpose that it, that it was being used.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Germans occupied Hungary in, around, shortly before April 15th, and they decided to finish the job that the Hungarians did not do.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so it happened that we were picked up, and we were in the outlying areas that Horthy wanted to, wanted the Hungarians to pick up first-- not the Hungarians in Budapest, but the outlying areas that became Hungary in '38.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
